values:
I was receently looking at the the AFI's top 100 series and this year the theme is "100 cheers". This is bassically a cheep excuse to re-do the 100 films list over again, its just the movies have to have a happy ending.

So this got me to thinking, I allready did my top 101 so now im going to do the 50 greatest villians of cinema.

some of the best western, action, and drama, villians i've ever seen are going to be in this list, be sure not to miss it.

ok for those of you who don't know, I don't use live journal, cause it gets me real angry real quickly... and i don't like that. and its pretty oxymoronic to say that on live journal, but this is an announcment to say i'm comming to use LJ, but not as a journal... then what am i saying in a journalic announcment? I have come here to announce that the account I never really wanted, will be used as "Brent's Movie Review Land!"

Here I'll talk about any movie I've seen; most of which you've probably never have heard of, but not all! I intend on reviewing any movie i'm watching, whethere its a new one in theaters, or if its just some old movie I end up watching. Any ways, enjoy feel free to comment, in fact, be sure to comment so i know what everyone else thinks about the movies and\ or about my reviews. bottom line, have fun
